{
  "texts": [
    "Worldwide, it ranks as the second most common cause of death.",
    "Every year, about 10 million individuals die due to cancer (Lewandowska et al. 2019).",
    "It is estimated that 70% of deaths caused by cancer occur in countries with low to middle incomes.",
    "Approximately 3.7M lives could be protected every year through the implementation of appropriate strategies for prevention, early detection, and treatment.",
    "There is an estimate that the total financial cost of cancer is US $1.16 trillion per year (Eloranta et al. 2021)."
  ]
}